## Vercel Speed Insights Installation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for this Next.js project following the latest official documentation.

### Changes Made

**1. Installed Package**
- Added `@vercel/speed-insights` version 2.0.0 to dependencies
- Used npm to install the package, updating both package.json and package-lock.json

**2. Modified Files**
- **frontend/src/app/layout.tsx**: Added SpeedInsights component to the root layout
  - Imported `SpeedInsights` from `@vercel/speed-insights/next`
  - Added `<SpeedInsights />` component at the end of the body tag

### Framework-Specific Implementation

This project uses Next.js 16.1.6 with the App Router architecture. Following the official Vercel documentation:
- Used the Next.js-specific import: `@vercel/speed-insights/next`
- Placed the component in the root layout file for global coverage
- Component is positioned inside the `<body>` tag after the main content

### Testing & Verification

1. ✅ Build completed successfully with no errors
2. ✅ TypeScript compilation passed
3. ✅ No new linting errors introduced
4. ✅ All 11 routes generated successfully

### Next Steps

To enable Speed Insights on Vercel:
1. Navigate to your Vercel dashboard
2. Select "Speed Insights" from the sidebar
3. Choose this project
4. Click the "Enable" button
5. Deploy the changes to Vercel

Once deployed and enabled, Speed Insights data will appear in the dashboard within a few days of user traffic.

### Implementation Notes

- The SpeedInsights component is a lightweight client component that only loads when necessary
- It automatically tracks Core Web Vitals and page performance metrics
- No additional configuration is required for basic functionality
- The component is framework-aware and optimized for Next.js App Router
